.TH CLUN 1 "0.3.0" "Clun 0.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clun \- JavaScript and TypeScript toolkit in pure Common Lisp
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clun
[\fIglobal-flags\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.br
.B clun
[\fIglobal-flags\fR] \fIfile\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Clun is a JavaScript and TypeScript toolkit.
The implementation is pure Common Lisp.
Clun provides a runtime, package manager, test runner, bundler, HTTP server,
and related tools.
Command names and APIs follow Bun shape.
JavaScript is only what the user runs.
The Clun implementation is not Node, V8, libuv, Rust, Zig, or C.
.PP
This page uses the same command catalog as
.BR "clun --help"
.
The man page must match live CLI behavior.
Regenerate with
.B make man
after you change the catalog.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B clun <file>
Run a .js, .mjs, .cjs, .json, or .ts file.
.TP
.B clun run
Run a file or a package.json script.
.TP
.B clun -e / -p
Evaluate code. -p prints the result.
.TP
.B clun exec
Run a Clun shell script.
.TP
.B clun install
Install dependencies, or add packages and install.
.TP
.B clun add
Add packages (-d for dev, -E for exact) and install.
.TP
.B clun remove
Remove a dependency and install again.
.TP
.B clun publish
Pack and publish to npm (NPM_TOKEN or .npmrc).
.TP
.B clun build
Build a production bundle (Clun.build / Bun.build).
.TP
.B clun fmt / lint
Format or lint JS, TS, JSON, YAML, or CSS.
.TP
.B clun compile
Build a single-file executable.
.TP
.B clun tsc
Run structural TypeScript typecheck.
.TP
.B clun test
Run the test runner.
.TP
.B clun update
Verify and activate the latest Release bundle.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --cwd <dir>
Set the working directory.
.TP
.B --hot / --watch
Reload on change (--hot soft, --watch hard restart).
.TP
.B --filter/-F <p>
Filter monorepo packages by name or ./path.
.TP
.B --workspaces
Run a script in every workspace package.
.TP
.B --parallel
Run filtered scripts in concurrent topo waves.
.TP
.B --concurrency N
Set max concurrent workspace scripts.
.TP
.B --silent
Suppress console.log, info, and debug.
.TP
.B --backtrace
Show a Lisp backtrace on internal error.
.TP
.B -v / --version
Print the version.
.TP
.B --update
Same as clun update.
.TP
.B --check-update
Report if a newer Release is available.
.TP
.B -h / --help
Print this help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime or command error.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set, disable CLI color.
.TP
.B CLUN_FORCE_COLOR
If set, force CLI color.
.TP
.B INSTALL_VERSION / CLUN_VERSION
Pin the install release tag for the shell installer.
